Time limit 1 second
Memory limit 64Mb
Input: standard input
Output: standard output

The beauty of a line is the maximum number of identical letters in a row. (the beauty of the string abcaabdddettq is 3)

Make the string given to you as beautiful as possible if you can do no more than k character replacement operations.

Input format

The first line contains one integer k (0 ≤ k ≤ 109)

The second line contains a non-empty string S (|S| ≤ 2 ⋅ 105). The S line consists only of small Latin letters.

Output Format

Print one number - the maximum possible beauty of the line that can be obtained.